00:20:57,660 --> 00:20:59,420
淡定 我们手上有你了
Calm down. I've had it with you!!

319
00:21:10,020 --> 00:21:11,620
我不介意
I'm all right.

320
00:21:12,540 --> 00:21:16,260
我想念我的使命了
I missed my vocation.

321
00:21:16,260 --> 00:21:19,460
怀疑脊柱断了
Suspected broken back.

322
00:21:19,460 --> 00:21:21,260
其它和我们估计的一样
Everything else just as we thought.

323
00:21:21,260 --> 00:21:23,220
-泰勒 -在
-Taylor. -Sir.

324
00:21:23,220 --> 00:21:25,700
他们告诉我你喜欢摔跤
They tell me you're a wrestling fan. 

325
00:21:25,700 --> 00:21:28,780
哦，我妈喜欢，我只是为了带她去罢了
Oh, well, me mam is sir, I just take her along, like.

326
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:31,620
切克・谢弗斯听说过吗？
Name Chick Shavers mean anything to you?

327
00:21:31,620 --> 00:21:34,380
对，我在波维克见过他一次…
Oh, aye, I saw him in Berwick once...

328
00:21:34,380 --> 00:21:37,300
他现在退休了，膝盖不行了。他是块难啃的骨头
He's retired now, did his knee in. Oh, he was a nasty piece of work.

329
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:38,820
不过干得非常不赖
Played the part well, though. 

330
00:21:38,820 --> 00:21:42,060
把波罗洲那个野人打得很惨
Did some horrible things to The Wild Man of Borneo.

331
00:21:42,060 --> 00:21:44,380
有一次几乎把他的背打断了
Nearly broke his back once.

332
00:21:44,380 --> 00:21:47,900
-谢谢你 -是
-Thank you. -Sir. 

333
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:53,660
如果我们把他拷起来，你觉得你能自己对付谢弗斯吗？
So if we cuff him, d'you reckon you can manage Shavers on your own?

334
00:21:55,180 --> 00:21:57,780
-当然能 -好的
Yeah, of course. Good.

335
00:21:57,780 --> 00:21:59,660
不过我应该…
Well, I should, um...

336
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:01,700
站在他够不着的地方
stay out of his reach though. 

337
00:22:03,740 --> 00:22:07,540
我反对纳粹来这里到处挥舞他们的钞票！
I object to Nazis coming here and flashing their money around.

338
00:22:07,540 --> 00:22:10,220
我反对。因为――我的钱在哪里？嗯？
I object, OK? Cos where's my money, eh? 

339
00:22:10,220 --> 00:22:12,500
我的呢？我以为我们是战胜国！
Where's mine? I thought we won the war!

340
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,500
现在是1964年了，谢弗斯先生
This is 1964, Mr Shavers.

341 

00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:17,620
你倒是腰包鼓鼓的！
There speaks a man whose pockets are full!

342
00:22:17,620 --> 00:22:20,580
听着
Listen...

