Look...

356
00:23:06,780 --> 00:23:09,020
冷静一下
Just calm down, all right.

357
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:13,700
我们接着来
Just get on with it.

358
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:15,580
好了
All right.

359
00:23:15,580 --> 00:23:17,340
我的确去了码头，没错
I did go to the quayside, aye.

360
00:23:17,340 --> 00:23:19,700
不过是正要回来，这是实话
But I was on me way back, and this is the truth, right?

361
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:21,900
因为我承认我恨他们
Cos I admit it. I hate 'em.

362
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:26,900
我恨德国鬼子，不错，我确实想干点什么，我知道能干什么
I hate Jerries, and all right, I did want to do somet hing else and I knew what that something was, so I

363
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:30,980
所以我去了码头，准备松开他们的小船
went down to the quay to set their boat adrift.

364
00:23:30,980 --> 00:23:33,460
这时大概9点
This is about nine. 

365
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:38,340
我到他们那条豪华小船的时候周围没有人
And I arrive, and there's their flash boat with no-one around, or, I think

366
00:23:38,340 --> 00:23:45,460
或者我觉得没有人，然后我发现了一辆轿车，里面的人打开了灯，所以我转过了身
there's no-one around, but then I clock this car, cos whoever's in it turns on some light so I turn away.

367
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:47,380
等等，等等
Hang about, hang about.

368
00:23:47,380 --> 00:23:50,020
-那是谁？ -我不知道
-Who was it? -I don't know.

369 

00:23:50,020 --> 00:23:52,020
那你……你没认出他们？
Well, didn't...didn't you recognise them?

370
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:55,780
我又没在看！我是在等着把他们的船松开
I'm not looking, am I? I'm waiting to set the boat adrift.

371
00:23:55,780 --> 00:23:58,860
我只希望那个家伙走人，可他没走，就坐在那里！
I just want the bloke to go, but he stays, he just sits there!

372
00:23:58,860 --> 00:24:00,620
冷静
Calm down.

373
00:24:02,140 --> 00:24:08,060
等了半小时以后，我没兴趣了，放弃了回到酒馆
And after half an hour of waiting, I lose me appetite, give up, go back to the pub and

374
00:24:08,060 --> 00:24:13,460
我到那里时哈迪曼家和德国佬正在往家走。这都是大实话
arrive just as the Hardyments and the Kraut are heading off home. And that's the God's honest.

375
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:15,980
-那车是什么样的？ -我不知道！
-And what type of car was it? -I don't know! 

376
00:24:19,780 --> 00:24:21,540
一辆深色的沙龙
A da rk saloon.

377
00:24:21,540 --> 00:24:24,140
我不能肯定，我只能告诉你这么多
I can't be sure. That's all I can tell you.

378
00:24:24,140 --> 00:24:25,660
好的
Right. 

379
00:24:34,780 --> 00:24:38,860
我说切克・谢弗斯不是你的真名，对不对？
Would I be right in thinking that "Chick Shavers" isn't your real name?

380
00:24:38,860 --> 00:24:42,580
这是我的艺名，现在大家都叫我这个名字
Well, it's the name I used professionally. And i t's the one I'm known as now.

381
00:24:42,580 --> 00:24:45,420
好吧
Right, yeah, see,

382
00:24:45,420 --> 00:24:48,260
恐怕我们需要你出生证上的名字
I'm afraid we need your name that's on your birth certificate.

383
00:24:52,740 --> 00:24:55,740
-马尔科姆・费雷 -什么？
-Malcolm Fairey. -Sorry?

384
00:24:55,740 --> 00:24:58,300
马尔科姆・费雷
Malcolm Fairey!

385
00:24:58,300 --> 00:25:01,060
-谢谢 -娘娘腔
-Thank you. -Poofter.

386
00:25:03,740 --> 00:25:05,620
你知道，没有一个当地人…
You know, none of the locals...

387
00:25:05,620 --> 00:25:08,580
当然，除了蓝色角落里的那个“仙女”
Well, except for the Fairey in the blue corn er...

388
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:11,620
没有任何人说过我们这位德国轰炸机飞行员的坏话
none of them have a bad word to say about our Germ an bomber.

389
00:25:11,620 --> 00:25:14,820
是啊，冈特・施麦克似乎是个挺正派的人
Yeah, Gunter Schmeikel seems to have been a decent fellow.

390
00:25:14,820 --> 00:25:18,420
是啊，是啊，作为一个往人头上扔炸弹的人来说
Oh, yeah, yeah. For somebody who dropped bombs on people.

391
00:25:18,420 --> 00:25:21,860
你知道 我还记得那些被轰炸的码头
You know, I can just about remember the docks being bombed.

392
00:25:21,860 --> 00:25:23,500
平民被炸死
Civilians were killed.

393
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:25,060
无辜的群众
Innocent people. 

394
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:27,940
听说过德累斯顿吗
Ever hear of Dresden?

395
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:32,220
我们的轰炸机在那里制造的火风暴杀了5万百姓
Our bombs created a fire storm that killed 50,000 civilians.

396
00:25:32,220 --> 00:25:35,260
据我所知没什么特别的原因
For no particular reason that I can think of,

397
00:25:35,260 --> 00:25:37,660
只为了恐吓一个民族
except to terrorise a nation.

398
00:25:39,380 --> 00:25:44,260
德国人在发动该死的战争之前就该想到这一点
Yeah, well, the Germans should've thought of that before they started the bloody war.

399
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:48,140
对
Right.

400
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:52,740
切克・谢弗斯告诉我们在他离开时码头有辆车
Chick Shavers tells us that there was a car at the quayside when he left.

401
00:25:52,740 --> 00:25:57,140
-对 -等他回到酒馆时，哈迪曼一家正在对冈特说再见，
-Yep. -When he got to the pub, the Hardyments were saying goodbye to Gunter,

402
00:25:57,140 --> 00:26:02,780
然后哈迪曼家开车走了，在山上他们看到威尔海姆下来
and the Hardyments drive along the road, up the hill where they see Wilhelm coming down.

403
00:26:02,780 --> 00:26:04,900
对，他是一个人，没带他的妻子
Yeah, and he's on his own. He hasn't got his wife with him.

404
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:06,780
-根据哈迪曼家的说法 -对
According to the Hardyments. Yeah. 

405
00:26:06,780 --> 00:26:10,460
同时，冈特从酒馆走去了码头
Meanwhile, Gunter's walking from the pub to the quay.

406
00:26:10,460 --> 00:26:13,260
我们推测，他就是在那里遇到了杀他的人
We assume, where he met his maker.

407
00:26:13,260 --> 00:26:17,260
我们去看看施麦克他们什么时候回酒店的
Let's see what time the Schmeikels booked back into their hotel.

408
00:26:17,260 --> 00:26:19,020
-好 -应该很有意思
-OK. -Should be interesting.

409
00:26:25,340 --> 00:26:28,620
-查尔纳？ -你说了“不管醉的还是醒的”，头儿
-China? -Well, you did say "drunk or sober", Guv.

410
00:26:28,620 --> 00:26:33,100
不，不，巴克斯先生。我清醒得像只羊，准备并愿意
No, no, Mr Bacchus. I'm sober as a lamb, and ready and willing to

411
00:26:33,100 --> 00:26:39,700
去做任何詹特利先生准备并愿意让我去做的事
do whatever it is Mr Gently is ready and willing for me to do.

412
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:41,220
看来是醉的
Drunk, then.

413
00:26:41,220 --> 00:26:42,780
-泰勒 -长官
-Taylor. -Sir.

414
00:26:42,780 --> 00:26:50,220
去我家，把这个人擦洗干净，刮好胡子，给他穿上我的西装和衬衫，戴上领带
Go to my house. I want this man scrubbed, shaved and put in one of my suits, with a shirt and tie,

415
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:53,820
穿好鞋和袜子…我的袜子…然后再带回来
with shoes on, and socks...my socks...and brought back here.

416
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:58,060
詹特利先生，先生，我不能让其他男的靠近我…
Mr Gently, sir. I cannot let another man perform intimate...

417
00:26:58,060 --> 00:27:01,900
如果我乐意…
And if I'm pleased...

418
00:27:01,900 --> 00:27:04,860
擦洗，泰勒・・・从头到脚
Scoured, Taylor...head to toe.

419
00:27:04,860 --> 00:27:06,620
-越快越好 -是，长官
-Quick as you can. -Yes, sir.

420
00:27:08,140 --> 00:27:09,740
他名叫罗伯特・斯特拉顿
His name's Robert Stratton.

421
00:27:09,740 --> 00:27:11,860
他是国家公园的看守人
He's a warden for the National Park. 

422
00:27:11,860 --> 00:27:15,180
他昨天晚上在码头上，观察鸟类迁徙
He was on the quay last night monitoring bird migration.

423
00:27:16,700 --> 00:27:18,740
我只是复述，先生
I only know what I'm told, sir.

424
00:27:18,740 --> 00:27:21,300
他是自己来的
He came in of his own accord.

425
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:25,540
他带着他女儿一起来的，那就是她。他妻子身体不好
He's here with his daughter, that's her, cos his wife's not well,

426
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:30,100
他女儿明显有些…
and his daughter's apparently a bit... WHISTLES

427
00:27:30,100 --> 00:27:32,700
我们大概9点去了码头
We got to the quay around nine. 

428
00:27:32,700 --> 00:27:35,500
-对不起，夜里看鸟？ -对
-Yes... -Bird watching at night? Yeah.

429
00:27:35,500 --> 00:27:38,780
我们不是整年都看，只是在迁徙开始的时候才看
Oh, we don't do it all year round, just when the migrations are on.

430
00:27:38,780 --> 00:27:40,500
你不必非得看见它们，知道么
You don't have to see them, y'see...

431
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:42,500
能听见它们飞来了
you can hear 'em coming in.

432
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:47,020
有一个湖上出现了一对秋沙鸭，从丹麦飞来的
And we've had a couple of mergansers turn up on one of the lakes, from Denmark.

433
00:27:47,020 --> 00:27:51,340
红色的秋沙鸭是很邋遢的鸟儿，在这些地方不常见
The red merganser's a scruffy bird, it's not very common in these parts.

434
00:27:51,340 --> 00:28:00,220
它的脑袋很多毛，看起来乱糟糟的，总好像湿淋淋的…总是…总是…
It's got a tufty head, very untidy-looking, always bedraggled...always...always.

435
00:28:00,220 --> 00:28:01,780
就是它
That's the one. 

436
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:07,300
但是你昨天晚上没出去，只是坐在码头旁边的车里？
But you weren't out and about last night, you were sitting in your car on the quay?

437
00:28:07,300 --> 00:28:12,900
我选了个角度可以看到海，我没看到有人来肯定是因为我正在看海
Angled, yeah, so I'm looking out to sea, which is what I must've been doing cos I didn't see anyone arrive.

438
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:16,580
可突然这个大块头从停小船的地方冒了出来
But suddenly this big chap turns up, down by the dinghy moorings.

439
00:28:16,580 --> 00:28:20,060
他向我这个方向看了看，就转开了
He looks in my direction and turns away.

440
00:28:20,060 --> 00:28:23,300
他来回走了一阵子，好像很不耐烦
And he walks up and down a bit, impatient, like.

441
00:28:23,300 --> 00:28:25,900
后来我继续去观察天空，他走了
And then I'm checking the skies again and he's gone.

442
00:28:26,100 --> 00:28:31,140
-后来怎么了？ -有些麻鹬和蛎鹬来了
-And what happened then? -Well, some curlew and oyster-catchers come over.

443
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:34,180
我们对鸟不是很感兴趣
We're not greatly interested in the birds.

444
00:28:34,180 --> 00:28:38,320
哦，对不起……对
Oh, I'm sorry... No, um...

445
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:40,120
10点10分
Ten past ten, 

446
00:28:40,140 --> 00:28:41,900
又来了一个伙计
another chap turns up.

447
00:28:41,902 --> 00:28:43,740
这个瘦一些，非常高…
A slighter man, quite tall...

448
00:28:43,740 --> 00:28:48,900
恐怕我做不出更详细的描述，不过他坐在一根
I can't give much of a description, I'm afraid, but he's sitting on one of the

449
00:28:48,900 --> 00:28:52,880 
系船柱上，敲着大腿，好像在敲着一首歌的鼓点
bollards and he's tapping his thighs, you know, like he's drumming along to a song.

450
00:28:53,580 --> 00:28:57,960
然后…就像我说过的，我决定今天晚上不干了，回家了
And... Well, as I say, I'd decided to call it a day and I drive off.

451
00:28:58,360 --> 00:29:00,980
就是这个男的死了吗？
Was this the man who died?

452
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:02,260
等一下…
One minute...

453
00:29:02,460 --> 00:29:04,160
我能去拿一下护照吗
Can I go and get the passports?

454
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:10,700
爱丽丝！爱丽丝！不，别动这个
Alice! Alice. No. Stop it.

455
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:12,460
对不起
I'm sorry.

456
00:29:12,460 --> 00:29:14,940
给你，给你……
Here y'are, here y'are...

457
00:29:15,100 --> 00:29:18,720
把你这个月看到的鸟列个单子
Make a list of every bird you've seen this month. 

458
00:29:23,380 --> 00:29:25,900
你能及时来真是太好了
It's very good of you to have come in so promptly.

459
00:29:25,900 --> 00:29:29,100
你在码头上看到的就是这个人吗
Was this the man that you saw at the quay?

460
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:32,080
我的距离有点远
Look, I was some way away.

461
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:34,260
我不能肯定 嗯
I cannot swear to it. Right.

462
00:29:34,260 --> 00:29:36,780
这两个人呢
What about these two?

463
00:29:36,780 --> 00:29:38,660
他们在酒店
Yeah, they were at the hotel.

464
00:29:38,660 --> 00:29:39,880
好的
