00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:41,480
我下山的时候进去喝了杯酒
I popped in for a drink on the way down.

466
00:29:41,580 --> 00:29:47,760
他们就在酒吧里，很显眼  我回家的时候和这个人擦肩而过，他正在向码头方向走
They were at the bar, very smart. I passed this one as I was going home, he was coming down towards the quay.

467
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:50,060
他和什么人在一起吗？
Was he with anybody?

468
00:29:50,060 --> 00:29:51,960
不，是一个人，拎着两个袋子
No, he was on his own, he was carrying two bags.

469
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:55,020
对不起，她……给你  爱丽丝，松手
Oh, I'm sorry, she's... Here y'are. Alice, leave it.

470
00:29:55,020 --> 00:29:57,100
给你 接着写
There you go. Go on, carry on.

471
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:02,300
没事，没事
All right, all right...

472
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:04,220
我只想问你们几个问题，行吧
All I wanna do is ask you a few questions, that's all, right?

473
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:10,740
我只见过他两次，不过冈特就像是你认识了很多年的那种人
I only meet him twice, but Gunter, he is like someone you have known for years.

474
00:30:11,140 --> 00:30:13,580
他很…
He is so...

475
00:30:13,580 --> 00:30:15,980
你说话的时候他会看着你
He looks at you when you speak,

476
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:17,680
认真看着你
looks into you.

477
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:19,100
对你感兴趣
Is interested in you, 

478
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:22,620
那样的笑容
and has such a smile. 

479
00:30:22,820 --> 00:30:25,060
我觉得…
I think...

480
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:30,140

SHE SPEAKS ITALIAN Ma non tutti, ovviamente.

481
00:30:30,140 --> 00:30:34,420

Parla Italiano? No, veramente, no.

482
00:30:34,420 --> 00:30:36,760

Mia moglie e nata a Napoli.

483
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:39,060
哦……他结婚了
Oh...he's married, 

484
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:41,460
多可惜呀！
what a pity!

485
00:30:41,460 --> 00:30:44,540
冈特曾经跟我说过一次意大利语
Gunter, he spoke Italian to me once,

486
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:49,000
虽然他过去的妻子是……丹麦人
though his wife was, um...  Danish.

487
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:53,080
-过去？ -他告诉我她今年死了
-WAS Danish? -She died this year, he say to me.

488
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:57,080
-我妻子也是 -我真抱歉
-So did mine. -I'm so sorry.

489
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:01,180
冈特昨天晚上走的时候…
When Gunter left last night...

490
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:03,880
-和哈迪曼一家一起走的 -是，还有别人走吗
With the Hardyments. Yes, did anyone else leave?

491
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:06,540
那些不喜欢德国人请喝啤酒的人
The ones that don't like a German buying the drinks

492
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:10,280
先是出去了，后来又从另一扇门进来了
and have walked out, they come back in through the other door.

493
00:31:10,380 --> 00:31:14,360
我在酒吧里又忙了半个多小时，我一个人
I have been working the bar for half an hour or more, on my own.

494
00:31:14,460 --> 00:31:18,720
喝酒免费，切克也回来帮忙了
And the drinks are free, but now Chick is back to help!

495
00:31:19,220 --> 00:31:21,740
切克・谢弗斯什么时候回来的
And Chick Shavers came back when? 

496
00:31:21,940 --> 00:31:25,960
冈特和哈迪曼一走，切克就回来了
Gunter and the Hardyments go, and Chick is next to me straightaway.

497

00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:28,180
-然后留在这里了 -对。
-And stays here? -Yes.

498
00:31:29,780 --> 00:31:32,560
如果你想到
If you think

499
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:36,020
任何事要问我
of anything else you would like to ask me...

500
00:31:37,620 --> 00:31:39,140
谢谢
Thank you. 

501
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:45,000
给警察局打电话，他们可以放切克・谢弗斯走了
Call the station. They can let Chick Shavers go.

502
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:46,700
他有不在场证明
Got an alibi. 

503
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:50,840
詹特利先生，先生
Mr Gently, sir.

504
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:53,680
我们干的怎么样？我还行吧
How have we done? Will I do?

505
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:57,280
你有梳子吗，警长
Have you got a comb, Sergeant?

506
00:31:59,580 --> 00:32:00,780
给他
Give it to him.

507
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:05,140
你发现什么了
What did you find out?

508
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:09,800
里面有个人说向哈迪曼家打听一个叫茉莉的女人
Bloke in there says ask the Hardyments about a woman called Molly,

509
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:12,140
她在战争期间和他们住在一起
lived with them during the war.

510
00:32:12,140 --> 00:32:14,360
和冈特有点关系
And then had a thing with Gunter,

511
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:18,480
后来自杀了
and then she later topped herself. 

512
00:32:19,580 --> 00:32:21,320
查尔纳！跟我走
China! Come with me. 

513
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:24,700
不，你
No, you... 

514
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:38,440
查尔纳，那是我的西装，别把烟头掉在上面
China, that's my suit. Don't put fag-ends in it.

515
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:44,560
-好的，詹特利先生 -如果我把你假扮成一位警官，你起码得装装样子
-Right, Mr Gently. -If I'm passing you off as a police officer, at least try and act like one.

516
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:54,940
我有个问题
I have a problem. 

517
00:32:55,840 --> 00:33:01,060
哈迪曼家的人记得开车超过了你，施麦克先生 只有你一个人
The Hardyments only remember driving past you, Mr Schmeikel. You alone,

518
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:03,200
没有施麦克夫人
not Mrs Schmeikel.

519
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:07,540
她是和我在一起
She was with me!

520
00:33:09,180 --> 00:33:11,080
我在……我和他在一起
I was there... I was with him.

521
00:33:11,580 --> 00:33:15,980
另一个证人只见到施麦克先生下山
Another witness only saw Mr Schmeikel walking down the hill.

522
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:19,260
他们撒谎
They are lying! 

523
00:33:19,760 --> 00:33:21,580
他们为什么撒谎
Why would they do that?

524
00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:23,220
现在是谁在做调查
Who is the investigator here?

525
00:33:24,650 --> 00:33:28,500
也许哈迪曼家想指责我，因为他们指责过我了
Perhaps the Hardyments wish to point the finger at me because they did it.

526
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:31,300
对不起，你是在指责哈迪曼家吗？
Um, I'm sorry, are you accusing the Hardyments?

527
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,240
对！为什么不
Yeah! Why not?

528
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:35,120
他们喝醉了，他们杀了他！
They get drunk and they kill him!

529
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:39,100
-威尔海姆，别  -因为什么原因杀他，施麦克先生
Wilhelm, nein. -Kill him for what reason, Mr Schmeikel?

530
00:33:40,700 --> 00:33:43,320
因为他是德国人
For being German,

531
00:33:43,420 --> 00:33:49,140
而且很成功，你们无法忍受因为我们比你们更坚定
and successful, a combination you cannot bear because we are more determined than you,

532
00:33:49,140 --> 00:33:52,640
更勤奋，更有独创性，这让你们生气
more industrious, more ingenious, and this makes you angry.

533
00:33:55,380 --> 00:33:57,620
哦，不可能，对不起，我忘了
Oh. Not possible. I'm sorry, I forgot. 

534
00:33:57,820 --> 00:34:04,980
你们英国人是这么开心
You British are so pleasant. SHE SPEAKS GERMAN

535
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:07,160

HE REPLIES IN GERMAN

536
00:34:07,060 --> 00:34:08,500
随他们去
Leave 'em to it.

537
00:34:11,600 --> 00:34:13,700
我替我丈夫道歉
I apologise for my husband. 

538
00:34:14,200 --> 00:34:15,520
他很生气
He is upset.

539
00:34:16,620 --> 00:34:21,220
不过我很好奇，你觉得哈迪曼家是出于什么
I'm curious, though, as to what motive you think

540
00:34:21,220 --> 00:34:26,940
动机把这件事归咎于你，如果他们认为是你杀了你父亲？
the Hardyments would attribute to you, if they thought you had killed your father.

541
00:34:28,820 --> 00:34:30,660
-这个问题太扯了！ -威尔海姆
-Ridiculous question. -Wilhelm.

542
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:33,380
你们是不是认为我们现在是嫌疑犯
Are you considering us now suspects? 

543
00:34:37,820 --> 00:34:40,100

Britische Gerechtigkeit!

544
00:34:40,100 --> 00:34:44,420

THEY SPEAK ANGRILY IN GERMAN

545
00:34:55,100 --> 00:34:56,120
你都听到了？ 
Did you get all that? 

546
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:58,880
她叫他别粗鲁…
She asked him not be rude...

547
00:34:59,150 --> 00:35:04,100
然后他就爆粗了……他还告诉她
And then he was rude, and he told her to

548
00:35:04,100 --> 00:35:06,120
从现在起别管了
leave it to him from now on. 

549
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:07,980
他们吵了一架
They were having a row.

550
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:10,360
-我看是 -在那之前呢？
-I think. -And before that?

551
00:35:10,660 --> 00:35:16,540
她说哈迪曼家为什么要在他给了他们那么大一个好处的时候杀了他？
She was saying why would the Hardyments kill Gunter when he was making them such a generous offer?

552
00:35:16,540 --> 00:35:19,180
-什么好处？ -什么好处？-我怎么知道？
-What offer? -What offer? -How do I know?

553
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:23,440
他叫她闭嘴，再也别提这事
He told her to shut up and never mention it again.

554
00:35:23,540 --> 00:35:25,560
干得好，查尔纳
Well done, China.

555
00:35:25,620 --> 00:35:27,220
谢谢，詹特利先生
Thanks, Mr Gently.

556
00:35:27,260 --> 00:35:29,700
-也许还会需要你 -对，
-May be needing you again. -Yeah.

557
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:32,200
"Niemals" 意思是“永不”
"Niemals", it means never.

558
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:38,680
查尔纳没能离开敦刻尔克海滩
China never got off the beach at Dunkirk.

559
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:41,300
他在德国战俘营里呆了5年
He spent five years in various Stalags.

560
00:35:45,780 --> 00:35:47,900

DOGS BARK AND GEESE QUACK

561
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:57,040
把凳子拖出来
Pull up the crates.

562
00:35:59,100 --> 00:36:02,880
你们也许觉得之前已经吃过这个了 不过，给你们上一课
Now, yer might think this is what yer had before...but there's a lesson in that.

563
00:36:03,050 --> 00:36:05,080
拉长你们两次来访的时间
Put days between yer visits.

564
00:36:06,980 --> 00:36:08,580
我不要 谢谢
None for me... Thank you very much.

565
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:10,020
好了 坐吧 坐吧
Oh, yeah, man. Tuck in, tuck in.

566
00:36:11,370 --> 00:36:12,500
你们带来什么消息了吗？
Are yer back with news?

567
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:14,960
只有更多的问题
Just some questions.

568
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:18,880
好吧 我们喜欢来点儿智力测验 开始吧
Aye, well, we like a bit of a quiz. So fire away. 

569
00:36:19,110 --> 00:36:20,780 
茉莉是谁？
Who's Molly?

570
00:36:24,380 --> 00:36:26,600
谁跟你们说茉莉的？
Who talked to you about Molly?

571
00:36:26,670 --> 00:36:28,200
为什么不跟我们说说她？
Why don't you just tell us about her?

572 
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:33,500
吉米，坐下 吉米 吉米！
Jimmy. Sit down. Jimmy... Jimmy! 

573
00:36:42,510 --> 00:36:44,600
茉莉是吉米的妈妈
Molly was Jimmy's mum.

574
00:36:44,700 --> 00:36:46,680
她是附近一个农场主的女儿
She was the daughter of a neighbouring farmer,

575
00:36:46,910 --> 00:36:51,340
当她怀了私生子时――那是1940年1月
and when she got pregnant, out of wedlock, this is January 1940,

576
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:54,160
她父亲把她赶了出去 王八蛋
the father kicked her out. The bastard.

577
00:36:54,360 --> 00:37:00,040
茉莉一直在学习当老师，挺有前途的，所以我和玛布丝收留了她
Molly was training to be a teacher, you know, something worthwhile, so Mabs and me, we took her in.

578
00:37:00,500 --> 00:37:04,160
吉米出生后，玛布丝照料他，好让她完成学业
And when Jimmy was born, Mabs looked after him, so she could finish her training.

579
00:37:05,060 --> 00:37:08,820
她后来成了个出色的老师，人家告诉我们
And she became a wonderful teacher, so we're told.

580
00:37:09,220 --> 00:37:16,400
后来战争结束了，两年以后的47年5月2日，谁也没想到
Then the war ended and two year after, '47, 2nd of May, nay-body saw it coming.

581
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:19,000
她自杀了
She took her own life.

582
00:37:19,100 --> 00:37:20,580
就在这个农场里
Here on the farm.

583
00:37:20,700 --> 00:37:22,520
就是冈特住的那个阁楼
Up in the loft where Gunter stayed. 

584
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:24,580
没有原因
No reason why.

585
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,660
没有遗言
No last note. 

586
00:37:26,740 --> 00:37:28,280
只有个空药瓶
Just an empty bottle of pills.

587
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:31,520
-冈特当时在哪里？ -被遣返了，两周前才回去
-Where was Gunter? Repatriated. -He'd gone back two weeks before.

588
00:37:33,320 --> 00:37:38,200
她是怎么死的，死在哪里，又是为什么    大家都在谈，胡乱猜疑
Aye, the how she died, and the where and the why got everybody talking, you know, making assumptions.

589
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:41,300
茉莉和冈特之间发生了什么吗？
Did anything happen between Molly and Gunter?

590
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:44,220
能回答这个问题的两个人都死了，不过…
Well, now, the only two people who can answer that are dead, but...

591
00:37:44,420 --> 00:37:47,150
我敢肯定他们之间肯定什么事也没有
I'm sure as damn-it certain nowt happened between 'em.

592
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:48,440
那么吉米呢？
What about Jimmy, then?

593
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:52,520
那时候他应该已经7岁了吧，茉莉死的时候？
He must have been about, I dunno, seven when Molly died.

594
00:37:52,820 --> 00:37:56,400
也许他看到他们……看到他们在一起，也许他知道什么事儿
Maybe he saw 'em... You know, saw them together, maybe he knows something.

595
00:37:56,950 --> 00:38:01,860
等冈特再回来的时候，对，大家又开始谈论了，说这和他有什么关系？
Look, when Gunter comes back again, aye, everybody's talking again, you know, was it to do with him?

596
00:38:02,060 --> 00:38:07,100
可他在这里的时间不长，只是在农场看了一圈 我们都跟在他后面
But he hadn't been here long, looking round the farm. We're all traipsing after him.

597
00:38:09,130 --> 00:38:11,680
一切都没变
Nothing has changed.

598
00:38:11,820 --> 00:38:13,380
什么都没变
Nothing.

599
00:38:13,380 --> 00:38:17,820
全和从前一样 一切！
All is as it was. Everything!

600
00:38:18,220 --> 00:38:22,040
只有我们 我们变了！
Only us...we have changed!

601
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:24,100
看看你们大伙
Look at you all!

602
00:38:24,430 --> 00:38:26,600
吉米
Jimmy...

603
00:38:26,700 --> 00:38:29,500
你才这么大
You were that size!

604
00:38:31,500 --> 00:38:34,540
还有你妈妈，茉莉
And your mother, Molly.

605
00:38:34,540 --> 00:38:36,400
她现在在哪里
What is she now?

606
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:41,200
她是校长了？一定是个好老师
She's a head teacher? Must be such a fine teacher.

607
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:43,380
我也能见到她吗
Will I get to see her, too?

608
00:38:43,380 --> 00:38:45,220
不能，嗯
No, um...

609
00:38:46,420 --> 00:38:49,380
妈妈很久之前就不在了，冈特
We lost Mum a long time ago, Gunter.

610
00:38:50,680 --> 00:38:52,920
那么多双眼睛盯着他看
'He had all these pairs of eyes staring at him,

611
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:55,840
寻找内疚的痕迹，哪怕是一丝的良心发现
'looking for a hint of guilt, a trace of bad conscience,

612
00:38:56,640 --> 00:38:58,900
可我们看到的只有爱和悲伤
'and all we saw was love and sadness.'

613
00:38:59,680 --> 00:39:01,020
和我们所有人的感觉一样
Same as what we all felt.

614
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:05,500
后来他在她自杀的那个阁楼里住了两个晚上
And yet, he spent two nights in the loft where she killed herself.

615
00:39:05,700 --> 00:39:09,400
-可我们没告诉他她死在哪里 -我能看看吗
-Yeah, but we didn't tell him that's where it happened. -Mind if I have a look?

616
00:39:10,500 --> 00:39:11,520
没什么可看的
There's not much to see, like.

617
00:39:22,410 --> 00:39:23,500
到了
There you go. 

618
00:39:31,850 --> 00:39:34,300
像我说的，没什么可看的
Like I said, not much to see.

619
00:39:47,100 --> 00:39:48,860
先生
Sir...

620
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:58,020
那是冈特的  一定是他落在这里的
That's Gunter's. He must've left it here.

621
00:39:58,250 --> 00:40:01,800
-他去酒馆没带？ -应该没有 肯定是他放这儿了
-He didn't take it to the pub? -Can't have. He must've left it here.

622
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:06,800
-指纹 -指纹？你要指纹做什么？
-Fingerprints. -Fingerprints! What do you want fingerprints for?

623
00:40:06,940 --> 00:40:10,200
冈特在这里的时候有没有说要给你们什么好处？
Did Gunter make you any kind of offer while he was here?

624
00:40:10,300 --> 00:40:12,100
谁告诉你的？
Who told you that? 

625
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:16,260
-有没有 -这个，我不是很明白他的意思
-Did he? -Well, I didn't really understand what he was on about.

626
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:20,240
说什么给免费给我们他公司的股票
Something to do with him giving us shares in his firm for free.

627
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:23,370
可我不喜欢股票的说法，所以拒绝了
But I didn't like the sound of shares, so I said no.

628
00:40:23,780 --> 00:40:27,240
可他不断地提起，说要感谢我为他所做的一切
But he kept bringing it up, saying he wanted to thank me for what I did for him.

629
00:40:28,140 --> 00:40:30,800
我对他说口头感谢就足够了
And I said to him words are enough.

630
00:40:30,980 --> 00:40:32,440
你为他做了什么？
What did you do for him?

631
00:40:32,740 --> 00:40:38,640
照我看没什么，可他说是我们中的一份子
Nowt, as far as I was concerned, but he said it was the community.

632
00:40:38,890 --> 00:40:40,660
我们生活的方式
The way we lived.

633
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:45,740
你不像之前那么友好了
You're not looking as friendly as you were.

634
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:49,160
我需要农场所有人的指纹，谢谢
I'd like the fingerprints of everybody on the farm, please.

635
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:55,600
-你的车在哪里？ -还在警察局
-Where's your car? -Still at the station.

636
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:59,620
去取了你的车，把卡艾纳从酒吧救出来，给自己挣点加班费
Pick it up, scrape China off the bar and earn yourself some overtime.

637
00:40:59,700 --> 00:41:03,220
把那个钱包清理干净，检查上面的指纹
I want that wallet dusted and cross-checked for fingerprints.

638
00:41:03,320 --> 00:41:08,060
找出任何可疑之处，以及施麦克一家和他们的公司的一切
Find out anything and ever ything that you can about the Schmeikels and their company...

639
00:41:08,060 --> 00:41:10,260
顺便说下这也是找卡艾纳的地方
That's where China comes in, by the way.

640
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:12,480
给德国大使馆打电话
Get on the phone to the German Embassy.

641
00:41:12,580 --> 00:41:17,000
我想要了解下这个公司 从商业中可以了解一个人
I want a flavour of this company. The business will reflect the man.

642
00:41:24,700 --> 00:41:27,720
谢谢你一直以来的照顾
Thanks. For the overtime.

643
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:32,940
话说回来 谁给我们引向茉莉的线索的
By the way, who gave us the heads up on Molly?

644
00:41:33,370 --> 00:41:36,860
伯特高尔特 把眼珠子钓上来的那个渔夫
Bert Galton. The fisherman that hooked out the eyeball.

645
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:38,060
嗯
Yeah

646
00:41:38,660 --> 00:41:40,680
奇科沙文思的朋友
Friend of Chick Shavers.

647
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:42,360
那现在还是吗
Is he now?

648
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:50,250
总督察
Chief Inspector.

649
00:41:51,010 --> 00:41:53,160
想要点什么
What can I get you?

650
00:41:53,020 --> 00:41:55,980
不用了 谢谢 我有公务在身
No. No, thank you, I'm on duty.

651
00:41:59,850 --> 00:42:04,860
我想知道那晚你有没有注意到...
I wondered if you noticed the other night whether...

652
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:08,420
甘特斯科美克是不是从他钱包里拿钱来付酒钱的
Gunter Schmeikel paid for his drinks from a wallet?

653
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:11,620
钱包 是的
A wallet? Yes, he did.

654
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:14,180
伯特高特...他在吗
Bert Galton...is he here?

655
00:42:16,210 --> 00:42:18,980
你知道 我下周末就离开了
You know, I leave at the end of next week.

656
00:42:18,980 --> 00:42:25,200
（她说的意大利语）而且我好奇...
SHE SPEAKS ITALIAN And I was wondering...

657
00:42:25,340 --> 00:42:29,580
你妻子给你做过意大利调味饭吗
Did your wife ever make you risotto di zucca?

658
00:42:29,580 --> 00:42:31,780
做过 经常做
Yes, she did, often.

659
00:42:31,780 --> 00:42:33,200
我说错话了
I have said the wrong thing.

660
00:42:33,220 --> 00:42:37,420
没有 额...
No. No, er...

661
00:42:40,160 --> 00:42:45,160
阿玛达 你是个很可爱的人 能认识你很高兴
Amata, you seem like a very lovely woman and it's been a pleasure to meet you.

662
00:42:45,220 --> 00:42:47,220
但我现在得走了
But I have to go now.

663
00:42:48,430 --> 00:42:49,880
祝你好运 詹特利先生
Good luck, Mr Gently.

664
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:01,800
哦 长官 尸检报告
Oh, sir, post mortem.

665
00:43:02,050 --> 00:43:05,440
下面的脊柱因为压力而粉碎了 不是因为击打
The lower spine has splintered from pressure, not a blow.

666
00:43:05,440 --> 00:43:10,260
对此他们还会做进一步检查 小伙子们还在取钱包上的指纹
They're gonna do more tests on that. The fingerprint boys are still working on the wallet. Too slow!

667
00:43:10,660 --> 00:43:12,700
我已经训斥过他们了 长官 你听听这个
I have bollocked them, sir, but listen to this.

668
00:43:12,750 --> 00:43:17,700
不来梅港市的德国警察正在调查威尔海姆斯科美克的欺诈事件...重大的欺诈案
German Police in Bremen are investigating Wilhelm Schmeikel for fraud...major fraud.

669
00:43:17,910 --> 00:43:22,800
- 他干了啥 - 他从他父亲的公司非法转出一些资金到他的账户里
- What's he been up to? - Illegal transfer of funds from his father's company into his accounts.

670
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:25,220
为什么他要偷他父亲的钱呢
Why would he need to steal from his father?

671
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:30,300
因为甘特正打算将他的公司转为合作机构
Because Gunter was in the process of turning his company into a co-operative,

672
00:43:30,300 --> 00:43:32,820
让每个员工都成为股票持有人
making every employee into a shareholder

673
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:37,680
- 这样威尔海姆就不是有效继承人了 - 把他带来
- and effectively...disinheriting Wilhelm! Pick him up!

674
00:43:38,980 --> 00:43:41,580
打鼾声
< SNORING

675
00:43:43,260 --> 00:43:46,720
头儿 紧急电话 港岸有纠纷
Guv, urgent call. Disturbance at the Mariners Rest.

676
00:43:46,940 --> 00:43:51,060
- 狗屎 - 你才是狗屎  -还跟我犟啊 
- Piece of shite! - Piece of shite yerself. - Spreadin' lies about my ma!

677
00:43:56,240 --> 00:43:57,740
扁他 伙计
Clip him, man!

678
00:44:00,300 --> 00:44:05,080
- 你给我少管闲事 - 他告诉你的 对吧 
- Keep out of this, you! - He's the one telling yer, is he?!

679
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:08,360
- 你被记录在案了 你们俩都是 - 你这是在鼓动吧
- You're nicked, the pair of you! - Bit of a mover, aren't ya?!

680
00:44:08,460 --> 00:44:10,000
拷上他 打电话求援
Cuff him, call for assistance.

681
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:13,580
走开 伙计们 让他们打完 笑声
Away, man, let them finish it! LAUGHTER

682
00:44:14,580 --> 00:44:17,620
我听说你有点头绪了 总督察
I hear you've had a bit of a result, Chief Inspector.

683
00:44:17,620 --> 00:44:22,460
我听说...小纳粹杀了老纳粹
I hear...the young Nazi killed the old Nazi.

684
00:44:22,490 --> 00:44:25,020
很高兴未被监禁
Joy unconfined, eh!

685
00:44:25,020 --> 00:44:27,140
闭嘴
Shut up.

686
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:29,660
费恶瑞先生
Mr Fairey.

687
00:44:31,660 --> 00:44:34,940
- 是谁负责管辖这块的 - 不是我 长官
- Who's been doing all the talking round here? - Not me, sir.

688
00:44:35,040 --> 00:44:39,800
那就让它立即停止 听到没 ... 你仍然在我的雷区内
Well, cut it out, d'you hear me! ..You are still on my radar.

689
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:58,900
他扔下他的妻子跑了 现正在去纽卡斯尔的公车上 试图弄条船
He ditched his wife and scarpered. He's on the bus to Newcastle. He's gonna try and get a boat!

690
00:44:59,200 --> 00:45:02,620
- 我以为你拿了他的护照 - 双重国籍 头儿
- I thought you took his passport? - Dual nationality, sir.

691
00:45:02,620 --> 00:45:06,040
- 他还有个丹麦护照 - 他母亲是丹麦人 阿玛达告诉我的
- He's got a Danish one an' all. - His mother was Danish. Amata told me.

692
00:45:13,500 --> 00:45:15,000
我试过阻止他
I tried to stop him.

693
00:45:15,530 --> 00:45:17,400
但你没打电话给我们 不是吗
Didn't telephone us, though, did you?

694
00:45:17,500 --> 00:45:21,820
我告诉过他这样会使事情看上去更糟 这会把你牵进来
I told him this will only look bad, this will implicate you!

695
00:45:22,540 --> 00:45:25,380
你英语很好 不是吗
Your English is excellent, isn't it?

696
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:29,880
好吧 这暂且搁一边 我们先澄清另一件事
Yes. Well, while we're at it, let's clear up one other thing.

697
00:45:29,880 --> 00:45:33,240
你到底有没有和你丈夫一起去码头
Did you, or did you not, walk down to the quayside with your husband?

698
00:45:34,210 --> 00:45:35,840
我本来是要去的
I was going to.

699
00:45:37,180 --> 00:45:41,220
但是我感到不舒服 需要躺一会儿 所以...
But I was feeling ill. I needed to lie down for a while, so...

700
00:45:41,420 --> 00:45:45,140
我待在了宾馆 他去了
I stayed here at the hotel and he went on ahead.

701
00:45:46,740 --> 00:45:49,040
收拾下东西 下楼来
Collect your things and come downstairs, please.

702
00:46:11,780 --> 00:46:14,420
慢慢来 喘息声
Take your time. OFFICER PANTS

703
00:46:14,620 --> 00:46:16,100
也别慢的这么久
Not that long!

704
00:46:16,300 --> 00:46:21,580
车站有人打电话说国家公园的守门人看到过甘特斯科美克
The station called to say a warden from the National Park claims to have seen Gunter Schmeikel.

705
00:46:21,680 --> 00:46:24,760
- 斯卓登吗 昨天已经找过他了 - 不是的 长官
- Stratton? We talked to him yesterday. - No, sir.

706
00:46:24,960 --> 00:46:29,020
是另一个守门人 说是今早在报上看到死者的照片的
Another warden, who saw the dead man's photo in the paper this morning

707
00:46:29,020 --> 00:46:32,680
想起来两天前在哈德良长城附近的公园里看到过他
and remembers seeing him in the park near Hadrian's Wall two days ago.

708
00:46:32,780 --> 00:46:36,380
他和一群人在一块儿 但是看到甘特斯科美克
He was with a group of people, but Gunter Schmeikel was seen

709
00:46:36,380 --> 00:46:40,000
和斯卓登在讲话 然后一起离开了 长官
in conversation with Stratton, who then went off with him, sir.

710
00:46:42,580 --> 00:46:46,500
在你之前到的那个男人就在不久前的一个晚上走了
The man who arrived just before you left the other night.

711
00:46:46,700 --> 00:46:52,180
- 我们怀疑那人是甘特斯科美克 你说他是坐在一个船柱上的 是哪一个 - 那个
- The man we assumed was Gunter Schmeikel, you said he sat on a bollard. Which one? - That one there.

712
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:55,660
- 所以车子几乎是正对着他的 - 对
- So the car's pointing virtually straight at him? - Yes.

713
00:46:55,860 --> 00:47:00,460
当你发动引擎是 车前灯亮了 他就正好在灯发出的光线中
And when you start your engine, the headlights come on and he's right in your beam?

714
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:04,680
- 应该是吧 对的 - 他大概在往上看
- I suppose so. Yes. - And presumably looks up.

715
00:47:05,280 --> 00:47:07,840
- 可能吧 我不记得了 - 是还是不是
- If he did, I don't remember. - Well, did he or didn't he?

716
00:47:07,840 --> 00:47:10,440
- 他就在你正前方 - 我当时正打算开车走人
- You were looking straight at him. - Well, I was driving off.

717
00:47:11,040 --> 00:47:15,440
对 要离开你得倒车然后再向前走
Yes, and in order to leave, you have to go into reverse and then come forward again.

718
00:47:15,540 --> 00:47:17,260
我倒车时是看着后面的
When I reverse, I look behind us.

719
00:47:17,460 --> 00:47:21,140
你的一个看门的同事说
A colleague of yours, a fellow warden, says that

720
00:47:21,140 --> 00:47:25,520
两天前看到你和甘特斯科美克一起在国家公园里
he saw you two days ago with Gunter Schmeikel at the National Park.

721
00:47:25,820 --> 00:47:29,200
他说你和他讲话了 然后和他一起离开了
He says you spoke to him, then went off together on your own.

722
00:47:29,200 --> 00:47:33,060
他说他是从报纸上的照片上认出死者的
He says he recognised the deceased from the newspaper photographs.

723
00:47:34,060 --> 00:47:36,660
不可能 不可能是同一个人
No. No, can't be the same man.

724
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:40,280
嗯 可是确实是的 不是吗
Well, it was, though, wasn't it?

725
00:47:41,480 --> 00:47:44,520
- 嗯 那天我见了很多人 - 很多德国人吗
- Well, I met a lot of people that day! - A lot of Germans?!

726
00:47:48,080 --> 00:47:52,180
听着 该怎么讲呢 抱歉 我从没把这两者联系到一块
Listen, what can I say? I'm sorry. I never connected the two men.

727
00:47:52,180 --> 00:47:53,520
现在你可以啦
Well, you can now.

728
00:47:54,220 --> 00:47:59,280
- 那个坐在船柱上的人和跟你一起离开的是不是同一个人 - 别对他吼
- The man who sat on the bollard, was he the same man you went off with on the moors?! - Don't shout at him!

729
00:47:59,780 --> 00:48:02,620
- 你为什么要吼 - 爱丽丝 别这样 求你了
- Why are you shouting? - Alice! Stop it, please.

730
00:48:02,620 --> 00:48:05,540
没关系 没关系 爱丽丝 你是对的
It's all right, it's all right. Alice, you're quite right.

731
00:48:05,540 --> 00:48:09,980
- 你是对的 我不应该吼的 - 你不该吼 一个叫詹特利的人是不该吼的
- You're quite right, I shouldn't. - You shouldn't. A man called Gently shouldn't shout!

732
00:48:10,080 --> 00:48:12,540
你是对的 爱丽丝 抱歉 我道歉
No. You're right, Alice. I'm sorry. I apologise.

733
00:48:13,440 --> 00:48:15,700
我爸爸有时也吼 不过只在屋子里
My dad sometimes shouts, only in the house.

734
00:48:15,700 --> 00:48:19,340
从不在外面 你不能在外面吼 只能在屋子里吼
Never outside, you mustn't shout outside, only in the house.

735
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:24,740
- 你责怪我们吗 - 没有
- Do you blame us? - No.

736
00:48:27,120 --> 00:48:30,380
我从没想到过...当然是同一个人了
It never occurred... Of course it was the same man.

737
00:48:30,780 --> 00:48:33,860
太感谢上苍了 要不然我们又要找另一个德国人了
Well, thank God for that or we'd be looking for another German.

738
00:48:36,720 --> 00:48:40,820
但是...你为什么要跟那个在公园里的人走呢
But...the man on the moors, why did you go off with him?

739
00:48:42,560 --> 00:48:45,820
嗯 每个人到那儿的人都想要看看秋沙鸭
Well, everyone was hoping to see a Merganser.

740
00:48:45,820 --> 00:48:50,180
吉姆 他本来是来见吉姆哈迪蒙特 但是吉姆这几天出去了
Jim, he was with Jim Hardyment, but Jim's got gout these days

741
00:48:50,280 --> 00:48:55,020
他问我能不能带他到湖那边 然后我就答应了
and asks if I can take him down the lake, so I said sure, yeah.

742
00:48:55,120 --> 00:48:58,680
我只是给他指了个正确的方向
I only point him in the right direction.

743
00:48:59,180 --> 00:49:02,260
我可能还会再找你聊 斯特拉顿先生
I may need to speak to you again, Mr Stratton.

744
00:49:02,660 --> 00:49:04,660
好的 当然 真对不起
Of course. Again, I'm sorry.

745
00:49:05,160 --> 00:49:06,620
我的心思都在这里
Me mind's all over the place.

746
00:49:06,720 --> 00:49:08,700
爱丽丝 你原谅我了吗
Alice. Am I forgiven?

747
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:21,500
追上了 追到了
Got yer. Got yer!

748
00:49:25,600 --> 00:49:29,500
喇叭响
HORN BLARES

749
00:49:40,940 --> 00:49:42,520
警察 对此我很抱歉
Police. Sorry about this...

750
00:49:42,520 --> 00:49:48,180
喂 站住 站住  很好 好的
Hey, you stay where you are! You stay where you are! Right? Yeah.

751
00:49:49,500 --> 00:49:52,920
怎么回事 额 你父亲发现你在偷他的钱
What happened, eh? Your father found out you were stealing from him?

752
00:49:53,020 --> 00:49:54,860
- 啊 - 好的 来吧
- Agh! - Right, come on.

753
00:49:56,060 --> 00:49:59,340
不好意思 只有我 局长有点忙
Sorry, it's just me. Chief Constable was busy.

754
00:50:01,980 --> 00:50:04,580
好了 现在你可以走了 谢谢 听着...
All right, you can go now. Thank you. Listen...

755
00:50:05,180 --> 00:50:06,740
不 不 不 去车里
No, no, no. In the car.

756
00:50:07,140 --> 00:50:11,380
拜托 拜托听我讲 这对我来说很重要对你来说也一样重要 拜托你能听我讲
Please. Just, please listen. This could be as important for you as it is for me. Please listen.

757
00:50:11,380 --> 00:50:16,220
- 现在你听我说 你不知道自己卷入了什么麻烦中吧 对吧 - 不 我当然知道 我知道
- No, you listen. You don't know how much trouble you're in? Right. - No, I know, I know.

758
00:50:16,620 --> 00:50:19,540
我知道 在这儿你们会把人吊死
I know, you hang people here.

759
00:50:20,740 --> 00:50:24,920
如果浪头扑向我 显然现在已经扑向了 那么没有人是会理解的
And if the tide is against me, which it is, then no-one is going to understand.

760
00:50:25,820 --> 00:50:29,640
现在我父亲的公司是我的了
So my father's company, mine now,

761
00:50:30,440 --> 00:50:33,120
我们可以以我们的方式来结算
we can pay our way!

762
00:50:35,860 --> 00:50:39,620
- 我没听懂 - 哦 不 你懂得 你很聪明 并且...
- I'm not following you. - Oh, yes, you are. You are very smart, and...

763
00:50:40,320 --> 00:50:41,120
并且我一直都有关注你
and I've been watching you.

764
00:50:41,320 --> 00:50:44,740
你有关系在警局 我并没有试图想要逃避什么
You have connections. And I'm not trying to avoid anything.

765
00:50:44,940 --> 00:50:48,140
只是 在德国 我们没有死刑
It is just that, in Germany, we do not have the death penalty.

766
00:50:48,240 --> 00:50:53,560
所以我所请求的就是你能够帮助我引渡 能把我送还到不来梅港市
So all I ask is for you to work on my extradition, to have me sent back to Bremen.

767
00:50:54,160 --> 00:50:57,620
如果你能帮我 我会给你20000英镑
For that, I will give you L20,000.

768
00:50:59,220 --> 00:51:03,520
因为我没有杀害我的父亲 没有 我没有
Because I did not kill my father! Did not, did not!

769
00:51:05,220 --> 00:51:07,260
听着...
Look...

770
00:51:07,260 --> 00:51:10,400
为表示我的真心 只要一个电话...
To show good faith, with one phone call...

771
00:51:10,600 --> 00:51:15,040
今天你的账号里就能多5000英镑
I put 拢5,000 into your bank account today.

772
00:51:15,540 --> 00:51:20,680
现在 我唯一需要的就是你的卡号 好吗
Now. All I need is you give me your account number. Yes?

773
00:51:33,580 --> 00:51:34,420
长官
Sir?

774
00:51:35,920 --> 00:51:38,280
- 斯科美克有什么消息吗 - 额 还没有 长官
- Schmiekel, any news? - Er, no, sir.

775
00:51:38,580 --> 00:51:41,320
- 验尸报告呢 - 也还没完成 长官
- Post-mortem tests? - No. Not yet, sir.

776
00:51:41,820 --> 00:51:45,740
我刚刚被告知甘特斯科美克的钱包上检测到两个人的指纹
I've just been told there are two sets of prints on Gunter Schmeikel's wallet.

777
00:51:46,040 --> 00:51:48,260
甘特和吉米哈德蒙特的
Gunter's and Jimmy Hardyment's.

778
00:51:50,740 --> 00:51:55,020
吉米...你能告诉我
Jimmy... Could you tell me, please,

779
00:51:55,020 --> 00:51:58,500
为什么甘特的钱包上有你的指纹吗
why your finger-prints were on Gunter's wallet?

780
00:52:02,920 --> 00:52:05,420
我拿它看一下里面有没有我妈妈的照片
I took it to see if he had a photo of me mam in it.

781
00:52:05,720 --> 00:52:06,520
什么时候的事
When was this?

782
00:52:07,120 --> 00:52:08,980
昨晚在酒吧的时候
In the pub on the last night.

783
00:52:10,900 --> 00:52:15,380
他唱着歌然后把外套扔给了我们
'He was singing this song and just threw his jacket to us.

784
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:18,620
他唱完时 我还拿着那个钱包
'But when he finished, I was still holding the wallet.'

785
00:52:22,880 --> 00:52:24,280
还没来得及看里面
Hadn't looked in it yet.

786
00:52:24,880 --> 00:52:26,840
防止有人看到...
In case anybody saw us...

787
00:52:27,340 --> 00:52:28,640
因为我觉得自己像个小偷
Cos I felt like a thief.

788
00:52:29,740 --> 00:52:31,060
所以我便把它收在身上
So then I kept it.

789
00:52:33,420 --> 00:52:36,740
我把钱包放在阁楼的床头柜上 不过他似乎忘拿了
I put it in the bedside cupboard up in the loft as if he'd forgotten it.

790
00:52:37,140 --> 00:52:39,660
那里面有你母亲的照片吗
And was there a photo of your mum in it?

791
00:52:42,230 --> 00:52:47,040
吉米 你认为甘特需要对你母亲的死负责吗
Jimmy, do you think Gunter was responsible for your mother's death?

792
00:52:55,240 --> 00:52:59,480
我知道威尔海姆和甘特的关系不好
I don't pretend that Wilhelm's relationship with Gunter was easy.

793
00:53:59,780 --> 00:53:01,320
一直这样
It wasn't.

794
00:53:02,120 --> 00:53:04,620
我想他们可能对一切事情的观点都不相同
I think, maybe, they disagree about everything,

795
00:53:05,540 --> 00:53:09,560
但是有一位成功的父亲 儿子是很难做的
but to be the son of a successful father, it is hard.

796
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:12,460
然后这次旅行中 他被引荐给这些...
Then on this trip to be presented to these...

797
00:53:14,160 --> 00:53:17,400
威尔海姆称他们为农夫...他们的确是
Wilhelm calls them peasants... and they are.

798
00:53:17,700 --> 00:53:19,460
从最好的层面来说 他们是农夫
In the best sense, they are.

799
00:53:19,960 --> 00:53:23,860
但是后来他父亲说 我们也应该成为这样的人
But then his father is saying, these people are what we must be like.

800
00:53:24,260 --> 00:53:28,780
我们的公司应该成为这样 我们应该这样互相照顾
This is what our company must be like, this is how we must look after one another,

801
00:53:28,880 --> 00:53:31,380
真的 这不关商业
and really, this is not business!

802
00:53:33,590 --> 00:53:36,180
你在哪里见到哈德蒙特的
And you met the Hardyments where?

803
00:53:36,280 --> 00:53:39,300
威尔海姆的父亲研究鸟类 哈德蒙特带我们去荒地的
Wilhelm's father studies birds and the Hardyments took us to the moors.

804
00:53:40,200 --> 00:53:41,300
跟我讲讲这件事
Tell me about that.

805
00:53:41,500 --> 00:53:42,880
没什么好讲的
There's nothing to tell.

806
00:53:43,280 --> 00:53:47,700
我们不喜欢哈德蒙特 我肯定哈德蒙特也不喜欢我们
We don't like the Hardyments and I'm sure the Hardyments don't like us.

807
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:50,360
但是甘特很开心
But Gunter is happy.

808
00:53:51,260 --> 00:53:52,060
非常开心
So happy.

809
00:53:54,360 --> 00:53:56,600
嗯 有人想要抢他的照相机
Well, someone tried to snatch his camera.

810
00:53:57,300 --> 00:54:00,140
没得逞 但威尔海姆十分生气
They didn't get it, but Wilhelm was very angry.

811
00:54:00,140 --> 00:54:04,200
他想找出这个人 因为事情发生在甘特离开河边时
He wanted to find this person, because it happened while Gunter was off at the lake.

812
00:54:05,100 --> 00:54:08,720
但是甘特说 算了 算了 然后我们就没追究
But then Gunter was saying, leave it, leave it, so we leave it.

813
00:54:10,020 --> 00:54:12,580
拜托了 我必须得重申 因为我知道
Please, I have to keep saying this, because I know it is true.

814
00:54:13,580 --> 00:54:18,500
威尔海姆绝不可能杀害他的父亲 绝对不会 这点我确定
Wilhelm could never have killed his father, never. This I know.

815
00:54:21,360 --> 00:54:27,800
你丈夫因从他父亲那里偷钱构成欺诈罪而被调查 弗 斯科美克 
Your husband is being investigated for fraud, Frau Schmeikel, for stealing from his father.

816
00:54:28,250 --> 00:54:33,000
可能是他预料到他父亲不会给他继承权 你知道这件事吗
Perhaps in anticipation of his father disinheriting him. Did you know that?

817
00:54:36,080 --> 00:54:38,380
他从没跟你讲过 对吗
He never told you, did he?

818
00:54:39,980 --> 00:54:42,820
好好想想吧
Do some thinking, please.

819
00:54:49,940 --> 00:54:51,800
- 詹特利先生 - 卡艾纳
- Mr Gently. - China.

820
00:54:52,750 --> 00:54:56,420
有人让我接了一个来自不来梅港市的电话 是那儿的警察打来的
I was asked to take a call from Bremen, from the police there.

821
00:54:56,420 --> 00:55:01,460
他们不会说英文 但是你得知道这个 半小时前
They couldn't speak English, but wanted you to know that, half an hour ago,

822
00:55:01,460 --> 00:55:03,980
威尔海姆斯科美克从他的银行账户里
Wilhelm Schmeikel instructed his bank

823
00:55:03,980 --> 00:55:08,580
转了5000英镑到约翰巴克斯警长的账户里
to transfer five grand into the account of Sergeant John Bacchus.

824
00:55:10,260 --> 00:55:13,800
他们想知道是否应该转这笔账
And they want to know whether they should let the transfer go ahead?

825
00:55:14,600 --> 00:55:17,640
- 巴克斯在哪儿 - 他刚进来 长官
-Where is Sergeant Bacchus? - He's just come in, sir.

826
00:55:17,640 --> 00:55:19,820
拷着那个德国人
With the German in handcuffs.

827
00:55:20,120 --> 00:55:22,580
- 他看上去很开心 - 头儿...
- Looking very happy with himself. - Guv...

828
00:55:23,580 --> 00:55:27,760
威尔海姆斯科美克想要录口供 我会为你安排好的
Wilhelm Schmeikel wishes to make a statement. I'll get him lined up for you.

829
00:55:27,860 --> 00:55:29,080
现在还不是时候 警长
Not yet, Sergeant.

830
00:55:31,080 --> 00:55:33,160
可以 让他们转
Yes. Tell them to go ahead with it.

831
00:55:34,460 --> 00:55:35,960
跟我走
With me, please.

832
00:55:41,280 --> 00:55:44,660
我 额...
I, er...

833
00:55:44,660 --> 00:55:47,400
在罗伯特斯特拉顿这人身上需要点你的意见
I want your opinion on Robert Stratton.

834
00:55:49,300 --> 00:55:50,580
可现在在这儿了 现在我们把这带来了
They're here now, we've got 'em now!

835
00:55:50,580 --> 00:55:54,100
我跟你讲让它随着时间溃烂得了
I'm talking about you letting it fester for years, man!

836
00:55:54,300 --> 00:55:57,040
在这个时候我觉得这样做最好 詹特利先生
I thought it was the best thing to do at the time! Mr Gently.

837
00:55:58,340 --> 00:55:59,900
看我们刚刚挖到了什么
Look what we just dug up!

838
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:03,440
- 我们需要尽快给威尔海姆录口供 - 你跟着我
- We must talk to Wilhelm as quickly as possible. - You stick with me.

839
00:56:03,740 --> 00:56:06,160
是我发现莫莉的 你知道的
I was the one who found Molly, y'see,

840
00:56:06,760 --> 00:56:10,280
她躺在床上 拿着这个盒子
and there she was, on the bed, holding this box.

841
00:56:11,980 --> 00:56:15,900
- 当我看到这些时... - 你本该看看内容或是告诉别人这件事
- And when I saw them... - You should've read them or told somebody about 'em!

842
00:56:15,900 --> 00:56:18,640
那样做不对 这些东西太隐私了
It wouldn't have been right. They were too personal!

843
00:56:18,640 --> 00:56:20,820
她又没有把它们藏起来 不是吗
She wasn't hiding them, was she?!

844
00:56:21,220 --> 00:56:26,220
我不想有人做些愚蠢的事 比如说去找那个让她做出这样的事的人
I didn't want anyone doing anything stupid like going after whoever had made her do such a thing. that's why I do that

845
00:56:27,120 --> 00:56:33,500
我把它们拿出来到她以前常坐的地方 然后我看了这些东西...后来把他们埋在了树下
I took 'em outside to where she used to sit and read and...buried 'em under a tree.

846
00:56:36,020 --> 00:56:37,840
你在胡说些什么
Now what yer blabbing for?

847
00:56:39,140 --> 00:56:41,950
因为他觉得甘特的事是我们的吉米干的 对吗
Cos he thinks our Jimmy did for Gunter, don't yer?!

848
00:56:42,150 --> 00:56:45,840
如果是吉米干的 那我们不都参与其中了 他跟我们在一起的
Well, if our Jimmy done it, we're all in it, aren't we? He was with us!

849
00:56:46,840 --> 00:56:50,260
这些都有将近20年了 我是说 这些能证明些什么呢
These must be nearly 20 years old! I mean, what are they gonna prove?!

850
00:56:51,460 --> 00:56:53,500
我们看看能证明什么 好吗
Let's find out, shall we?

851
00:56:54,500 --> 00:56:57,620
我不要打开它们 我不想知道这些信是哪里来的
I'm not opening 'em! I don't wanna know who they're from.

852
00:57:01,280 --> 00:57:02,000
我可以吗
May I?

853
00:57:07,140 --> 00:57:09,900
当你带甘特去荒地时
When you took Gunter out onto the moors,

854
00:57:10,600 --> 00:57:14,280
我想你见到过罗伯特斯特拉顿 其中的一个看门人
I gather you met Robert Stratton, one of the wardens.

855
00:57:14,280 --> 00:57:16,380
鲍勃斯特拉顿 是见到过
Bob Stratton, aye.

856
00:57:17,180 --> 00:57:21,120
甘特正跟我们讲他被击倒的那个晚上 然后鲍勃便加入了
Gunter was telling us about the night he got shot down, and Bob joined with.

857
00:57:21,920 --> 00:57:26,180
- 甘特后来跟他一起走了 - 嗯 我让他带甘特去湖边的
- And Gunter went off with him? - Well, I asked him to show him down to the lake.

858
00:57:26,780 --> 00:57:28,260
你认识罗伯特斯特拉顿多长时间了
How long have you known Robert Stratton?

859
00:57:29,060 --> 00:57:30,880
他是战后刚来这儿的
Came here just after the war.

860
00:57:31,180 --> 00:57:37,900
他来自桑德兰 （英国英格兰东北部港市） 他的生活可真悲惨 妻子精神一直不好 还有那可怜的姑娘 他的...
A Sunderland man. What a life he has, wife on the verge all the time and that poor lassie of his...

861
00:57:38,400 --> 00:57:41,200
他做了该做的一切 他是个好家伙
He does everything. He's a sound bloke.

862
00:57:46,580 --> 00:57:49,780
它们全被审查过 我是说 这上面线索寥寥无几
They're all censored. I mean, there's a few clues and that.

863
00:57:52,140 --> 00:57:54,980
如果看到电话亭 你介意停一下吗 我得打个电话 很快的
If we see a phone-box, d'you mind if I stop and make a quick call?

864
00:57:56,580 --> 00:57:59,000
- 有什么急事吗 - 没什么急事
- Something urgent? - No.

865
00:58:18,900 --> 00:58:21,440
- 你好 - 你好
- Hello. - Hello.

866
00:58:21,440 --> 00:58:24,360
- 我们可以... - 进去吧 进去吧 进去吧
- Can we...? Come in, come in! Come in.

867
00:58:24,960 --> 00:58:28,580
敲门声 有人吗 哦 哦 抱歉 抱歉
HE KNOCKS ON DOOR Hello? Oh! Oh, sorry. Sorry.

868
00:58:28,580 --> 00:58:31,180
水溅声 能给我们点时间吗 
WATER SPLASHES > Can you give us a minute, please?

869
00:58:31,180 --> 00:58:34,340
这是我妈妈 她就在里面
It's me mam, she's in the altogether.

870
00:58:34,340 --> 00:58:38,780
- 我妈妈 她在里面 你看 - 我们会等会的
- Me mam, she's in the altogether. Look. - Yeah, we'll wait.

871
00:58:38,780 --> 00:58:39,260
爱丽丝 进来 进来吧
Alice, come on. Pack it in! Come on.

872
00:58:39,860 --> 00:58:46,100
额 抱歉 我妻子现在不能自己洗澡或穿衣服
Er, sorry, me wife can't wash or dress herself at the moment.

873
00:58:47,100 --> 00:58:48,340
斯特拉顿先生
Mr Stratton.

874
00:58:48,340 --> 00:58:50,220
我本打算去找你的
Yeah, I was gonna come and see you.

875
00:58:50,520 --> 00:58:56,980
因为我意识到我之前也见过旅馆的那对年轻的德国夫妇
Cos I realised that I must have also seen that young German couple from the hotel before.

876
00:58:57,180 --> 00:59:02,180
在荒地时 和哈德蒙特家一起的 我是说那时我没跟他们讲过话 但是 额...
On the moors, part of the Hardyment group. I mean, I never spoke to them at the time, but, er...

877
00:59:03,880 --> 00:59:08,540
我猜他们也没认出我来 因为如果认出的话他们可能在旅馆时会说点什么的
I guess they didn't recognise me either cos they would've said something at the hotel, perhaps.

878
00:59:09,540 --> 00:59:16,880
那年轻的夫人说当甘特斯科美克跟你走了然后回来时
It's just that the young wife says that when Gunter Schmeikel came back from going off with you,

879
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:19,380
抱怨有人想抢他的照相机
he complained that someone tried to snatch his camera.

880
00:59:21,600 --> 00:59:23,640
什么 她说是...我没偷...
What? She said it was... I didn't steal...

881
00:59:23,740 --> 00:59:25,890
我干嘛要偷他的照相机 你听着
Why would I steal his camera? Now listen, no.

882
00:59:25,890 --> 00:59:28,120
不 他是个 他是个怪人
No, he was a, he was a strange one, that one.

883
00:59:28,520 --> 00:59:33,600
我并没有讲她指责是你干的 斯特拉顿先生 但请继续说
I didn't say that she'd accused you, Mr Stratton. But please go on.

884
00:59:33,900 --> 00:59:36,900
甘特斯科美克哪里奇怪了
Gunter Schmeikel was strange in what way?

885
00:59:37,800 --> 00:59:40,040
你知道的 他很奇怪...
Well, you know, he was odd...

886
00:59:40,840 --> 00:59:44,760
开始时很友好 但是当我们到达河边时
Nice enough to start off with, but when we got down to the lake,

887
00:59:44,760 --> 00:59:47,920
他转向我们 说"继续 继续"
he turns on us, "Go. Go on. Go on!"

888
00:59:48,820 --> 00:59:52,140
并开始说我在监视他
and starts saying I was spying on him.

889
00:59:52,140 --> 00:59:53,500
嗯 然后我就走开了 让他自己发疯去
Well, you know, I just walk away. I leave him to it.

890
00:59:54,400 --> 01:00:00,740
这个人在前一天下午行为那么古怪
And yet, this was the man who was behaving so strangely earlier in the afternoon,

891
01:00:01,740 --> 01:00:04,800
但在码头时你却没认出他
that you failed to recognise him at the quayside?

892
01:00:06,300 --> 01:00:08,920
是的 对此我已经做出过解释了
Yeah, well, I've already explained that!

893
01:00:08,920 --> 01:00:12,160
码头的人没让我联想到那个人 一次也没有
The man at the quayside didn't bring to mind that man, not once.

894
01:00:15,120 --> 01:00:16,800
意大利 44
Italy '44...

895
01:00:19,300 --> 01:00:20,820
达拉谟步兵团
Durham Light Infantry?

896
01:00:21,820 --> 01:00:23,740
是的
Aye.

897
01:00:24,960 --> 01:00:25,340
你呢
You?

898
01:00:26,040 --> 01:00:28,700
米德尔塞克斯团 然后...
Middlesex Regiment, then...

899
01:00:30,020 --> 01:00:32,000
..加入了柴郡团
..joined up with the Cheshire.

900
01:00:34,160 --> 01:00:35,980
应该对你们有点打击
Took a bit of a hammering.

901
01:00:37,080 --> 01:00:41,900
-是的 - 大部分时间我们部队都很平静
- They did. - We had a quiet time for the most part.

902
01:00:49,460 --> 01:00:53,060
- 抱歉 我觉得你的妻子... - 不
- Sorry, I think your wife's... - No.

903
01:00:53,060 --> 01:00:57,620
别 别 不 进来 进来
Come on. Come on. No. In. In. Come on.

904
01:00:57,720 --> 01:01:00,140
爱丽丝 不要这样 别这样做 爱丽丝
Alice, don't. Don't do that, Alice.

905
01:01:00,940 --> 01:01:04,380
爱丽丝 离火远点
Don't! Alice, come away from the fire.

906
01:01:06,120 --> 01:01:08,160
离火远点 这才是个乖姑娘
Away from the fire. There's a good girl.

907
01:01:09,760 --> 01:01:12,340
谢谢 谢谢
Thank you. Thanks.

908
01:01:14,340 --> 01:01:17,100
你工作时怎么办
What happens when you're working?

909
01:01:18,260 --> 01:01:19,900
他们待在房间里
They stay in their rooms.

910
01:01:21,700 --> 01:01:22,200
那是...
Does that...?

911
01:01:24,000 --> 01:01:25,120
他把她们锁起来吗
Does he lock 'em in?

912
01:01:33,860 --> 01:01:35,180
斯特拉顿是嫌疑人吗
Is Stratton a suspect?

913
01:01:35,780 --> 01:01:37,400
当然是的 怎么这么问
Yeah, of course he is. Why?

914
01:01:38,700 --> 01:01:41,060
那这会帮助你还是会阻碍你
Would that help or hinder you?

915
01:01:41,160 --> 01:01:44,800
- 不明白你的问题 - 那对你是有利还是有弊
- Don't understand the question. Would that be good or bad for you?

916
01:01:45,330 --> 01:01:46,540
对我
For me?!

917
01:01:48,800 --> 01:01:50,440
我糊涂了 头儿
I don't get you, guv.

918
01:01:51,240 --> 01:01:53,020
不来梅港的警察打电话来了
The police in Bremen rang.

919
01:01:53,420 --> 01:01:58,020
威尔海姆斯科美克往你账户里转了5000英镑
Wilhelm Schmeikel's transferring L5,000 into your account.

920
01:01:58,020 --> 01:02:00,780
- 我想告诉你的 - 嗯 你有两个小时的时间告诉我
- I was gonna tell ya. - Well, you've had two hours.

921
01:02:02,740 --> 01:02:04,140
我在等钱到位
I was waiting for the money to be in place.

922
01:02:04,140 --> 01:02:06,300
那会改变他的想法
It could've changed his mind!

923
01:02:06,700 --> 01:02:08,500
继续撒谎 警长
Try again, Sergeant.

924
01:02:09,500 --> 01:02:12,040
听着...
Look...

925
01:02:12,040 --> 01:02:18,060
好吧 我想向你证明我能以我的方式办好事情
OK, I wanted to prove to you that I could get things done, my way!

926
01:02:19,020 --> 01:02:20,780
头儿 拜托 听我说
Look, guv. Guv, listen, please.

927
01:02:20,980 --> 01:02:24,300
你想想 这家伙没想承认罪行 不是吗
Think about it! The guy wasn't just gonna go and confess, was he?

928
01:02:24,700 --> 01:02:25,840
那这就是证据
This is proof!

929
01:02:26,640 --> 01:02:30,940
- 这5000英镑会让他得到什么 - 20000 - 20000
- What was he gonna get for his 5,000? - 20,000. - 20?!

930
01:02:31,540 --> 01:02:34,040
现在只有五千 只要我把他送遣回国就能拿到剩下的钱
Five now and the rest when I got him extradited to Germany.

931
01:02:34,040 --> 01:02:35,360
你不能这么做
You can't do that!

932
01:02:35,360 --> 01:02:38,180
我知道 但是他不知道 不是吗
Well, I know that! But he doesn't know that, does he?

933
01:02:39,580 --> 01:02:42,120
他绝望了 绝望了 因为他有罪
He's desperate. He's desperate, because he's guilty.

934
01:02:42,240 --> 01:02:44,900
那吉米哈德蒙特以及哈德蒙特一家呢
What about Jimmy Hardyment and the Hardyment family?

935
01:02:45,000 --> 01:02:47,480
吉米的指纹遍布钱包
Jimmy's fingerprints are all over the wallet.

936
01:02:47,480 --> 01:02:49,900
你对罗伯特斯特拉顿的记忆间断就没有怀疑吗
Are you not bothered about Robert Stratton's memory lapses?

937
01:02:50,000 --> 01:02:52,620
长官 威尔海姆斯科美克杀了他父亲
Sir, Wilhelm Schmeikel killed his father,

938
01:02:52,620 --> 01:02:55,920
为了躲避这个 他试图买票回家
and in an attempt to avoid the news, tried to buy his way home!

939
01:02:57,120 --> 01:02:58,360
谢谢 对 很好
Thank you. Right. Very good.

940
01:03:00,460 --> 01:03:04,220
是的 我们现在需要把这5000英镑转回到...
Yes, we now need to transfer the 5,000 back to the...

941
01:03:05,640 --> 01:03:06,260
什么
What?

942
01:03:11,380 --> 01:03:12,500
多少钱
By how much?

943
01:03:18,000 --> 01:03:19,300
我一会儿回给你好吗
Can I call you back, please?

944
01:03:21,700 --> 01:03:23,180
谢谢
Thank you.

945
01:03:25,180 --> 01:03:28,820
你账户的钱不够退还5000英镑 只能退还
Your bank can't repay the full L5,000. They can only manage...

946
01:03:29,720 --> 01:03:32,040
4782英镑
L4,782.

947
01:03:34,180 --> 01:03:35,220
我的透支额
My overdraft.

948
01:03:35,220 --> 01:03:37,980
你所超支的金额最终被填补了
Which you exceeded and has consequently been cancelled,

949
01:03:37,980 --> 01:03:41,060
也就说 目前你受贿了
meaning, as of now, you just took a bribe.

950
01:03:41,980 --> 01:03:44,600
不 长官...你知道事实不是这样的
No, sir... You know that's not true!

951
01:03:44,600 --> 01:03:46,700
让我告诉你我知道什么吧
No, let me tell you what I know.

952
01:03:47,400 --> 01:03:50,700
你决定走捷径让威尔海姆的罪名成立
You decided to cut corners to incriminate Wilhelm Schmeikel,

953
01:03:50,700 --> 01:03:54,060
而你最后做到的是让自己变得有罪
and what you've really managed to do is incriminate yourself.

954
01:03:58,280 --> 01:04:00,700
找出这些信是谁写的
Find out who the man is in those letters.

955
01:04:01,500 --> 01:04:03,940
他的名字被黑掉了
His name is blacked out.

956
01:04:04,040 --> 01:04:05,660
他笑了笑
HE SCOFFS

957
01:04:06,350 --> 01:04:08,320
这个任务很简单 警长
It's a simple task, Sergeant.

958
01:04:08,820 --> 01:04:11,860
- 这信上记录了很多详细的东西 - 这事谁都能干
- There's lots of circumstantial stuff in them. - Anyone can do that.

959
01:04:11,860 --> 01:04:14,120
是的 那快去做啊
Yeah, so go and do it.

960
01:04:15,820 --> 01:04:18,850
- 这是对我的惩罚 是吗 - 我不在乎你怎么看待的
- My punishment, is it? - I don't care how you look at it.

961
01:04:19,700 --> 01:04:21,580
Just do as I tell you for once!!

962
01:04:21,580 --> 01:04:24,100
What are you gonna do while I'm stuck in some office

963
01:04:24,100 --> 01:04:26,180
30 miles away for the rest of the night?

964
01:04:26,180 --> 01:04:29,620
I'll talk to some senior officers who might just be able to save you

965
01:04:29,620 --> 01:04:32,860
from a dishonourable discharge from the police service!

966
01:04:32,860 --> 01:04:34,380
Hello.

967
01:04:36,540 --> 01:04:38,060
Speaking.

968
01:04:39,780 --> 01:04:41,500
Tomorrow?

969
01:04:41,500 --> 01:04:43,940
Just hold on a minute.

970
01:04:51,620 --> 01:04:54,380
Yes, that will be fine.

971
01:05:18,500 --> 01:05:19,820
Good work.

972
01:05:19,820 --> 01:05:22,060
Good work, Detective Sergeant Bacchus.

973
01:05:28,500 --> 01:05:29,860
Exc..

974
01:05:29,860 --> 01:05:31,580
Excuse me!

975
01:05:31,580 --> 01:05:32,740
Hello?!

976
01:05:32,740 --> 01:05:34,540
There's no need to shout in here.

977
01:05:34,540 --> 01:05:37,500
Can I move on to the Ss, please. Aye.

978
01:05:37,500 --> 01:05:39,380
Thank you. S for Stratton.

979
01:05:54,620 --> 01:05:59,420
Yes, I can feel myself inhabiting the role of the detective.

980
01:06:00,500 --> 01:06:02,540
Accumulating information,

981
01:06:02,540 --> 01:06:07,820
examining motives and evidence, you know.

982
01:06:07,820 --> 01:06:11,340
But I tell yer how I decide who's done it,

983
01:06:11,340 --> 01:06:17,180
cos it might be useful to you as a technique, y'know?

984
01:06:17,180 --> 01:06:19,820
Out of the mouths of babes in China...

985
01:06:21,700 --> 01:06:23,540
What I do is this -

986
01:06:23,540 --> 01:06:25,980
I ask myself,

987
01:06:25,980 --> 01:06:31,380
who would you not want to be right now, China?

988
01:06:31,380 --> 01:06:34,300
What's it like speaking German after all these years?

989
01:06:35,820 --> 01:06:37,860
It's not the speaking of it...

990
01:06:39,380 --> 01:06:41,340
It's hearing it again.

991
01:06:46,780 --> 01:06:48,460
So...

992
01:06:48,460 --> 01:06:52,380
Are you not going to ask me who I think done it?!

993
01:06:52,380 --> 01:06:54,860
Nope. I think you should get some sleep, China.

994
01:06:54,860 --> 01:06:58,300
German Police and Embassy officials first thing in the morning.

995
01:06:58,300 --> 01:07:00,820
Right, Mr Gently.

996
01:07:22,940 --> 01:07:24,660
Robert Stratton.

997
01:07:24,660 --> 01:07:26,500
Robert Stratton...

998
01:07:26,500 --> 01:07:30,260
"By the King's order the name of Corporal Robert C Stratton,

999
01:07:30,260 --> 01:07:31,700
"Durham Light Infantry,

1000
01:07:31,700 --> 01:07:35,260
"was published in the London Gazette on the 4th of August 1944,

1001
01:07:35,260 --> 01:07:39,980
"as mentioned in a dispatch for distinguished service.

1002
01:07:39,980 --> 01:07:44,340
"I am charged to record His Majesty's high appreciation."

1003
01:07:44,340 --> 01:07:46,180
Signed Secretary of State for War.

1004
01:07:47,700 --> 01:07:49,660
Mentioned in a dispatch for what?

1005
01:07:53,820 --> 01:07:57,380
Bloody hell! He killed three men with his own hands.

1006
01:08:00,260 --> 01:08:03,220
Ich flehe Sie an, bitte...

1007
01:08:03,220 --> 01:08:04,420
KNOCK ON DOOR

1008
01:08:07,740 --> 01:08:10,180
Ich moechte an die deutsche Justiz ausgeliefert werden.

1009
01:08:10,180 --> 01:08:13,940
Full post-mortem report, and DS Bacchus is on the phone for you.

1010
01:08:13,940 --> 01:08:16,700
Thank you. Taylor? Sir.

1011
01:08:16,700 --> 01:08:19,900
I sent someone to fetch Mr Stratton in. Is he here yet?

1012
01:08:19,900 --> 01:08:21,540
I'll go and check for you, sir.

1013
01:08:27,500 --> 01:08:32,140
Sir, I've got the identity of the man in the letters. Molly's man.

1014
01:08:32,140 --> 01:08:35,580
Right, he was based up here with the Royal Signals from '45

1015
01:08:35,580 --> 01:08:38,980
till he was posted to Palestine, where he died of diphtheria.

1016
01:08:38,980 --> 01:08:42,260
Now this was two weeks before Molly Hardyment killed herself.

1017
01:08:42,260 --> 01:08:45,860
And he was married, which may have some bearing.

1018
01:08:45,860 --> 01:08:49,340
Although, of course, none of this actually solves anything,

1019
01:08:49,340 --> 01:08:51,460
since the important thing is that people thought

1020
01:08:51,460 --> 01:08:53,900
it might have been down to Gunter.

1021
01:08:54,900 --> 01:08:57,460
D'you wanna say something, guv?

1022
01:08:58,980 --> 01:09:00,420
Well done. Well done.

1023
01:09:00,420 --> 01:09:03,740
Right. Am I still on the case?

1024
01:09:03,740 --> 01:09:07,140
You were never off it, or didn't you notice?

1025
01:09:07,140 --> 01:09:10,060
Sometimes we have to take the long way round, Sergeant.

1026
01:09:10,060 --> 01:09:12,740
Yeah, it's amazing what a bit of donkey work can do, innit?

1027
01:09:12,740 --> 01:09:16,180
Now, listen, I came up with one more thing. It's the...

1028
01:09:16,180 --> 01:09:18,940
Yeah, tell me when you see me.

1029
01:09:41,060 --> 01:09:44,060
Well? Doesn't look good, Mr Gently.

1030
01:09:44,060 --> 01:09:47,260
He's begging to be extradited... and admitting everything.

1031
01:09:47,260 --> 01:09:48,940
He admitted killing his father?

1032
01:09:48,940 --> 01:09:52,580
Well, he said he'd say he did it if they sent him back to Germany.

1033
01:09:52,580 --> 01:09:55,900
But then he said he didn't do it.

1034
01:09:55,900 --> 01:09:57,980
One thing's for certain, Mr Gently.

1035
01:09:57,980 --> 01:09:59,140
He don't want to hang.

1036
01:10:00,140 --> 01:10:02,860
Do you think he did it? Yes.

1037
01:10:02,860 --> 01:10:04,380
Well, no.

1038
01:10:04,380 --> 01:10:07,380
Well, maybe.

1039
01:10:09,020 --> 01:10:10,980
The Germans think he did it, sir.

1040
01:10:12,980 --> 01:10:14,020
Hm.

1041
01:10:15,420 --> 01:10:19,140
I ask you, Chief Inspector, if I wanted to kill him,

1042
01:10:19,140 --> 01:10:22,100
why wouldn't I have done it out at sea?

1043
01:10:22,100 --> 01:10:23,660
Claim it as an accident?!

1044
01:10:23,660 --> 01:10:25,620
You can't sail.

1045
01:10:25,620 --> 01:10:28,620
And your wife was with you.

1046
01:10:28,620 --> 01:10:30,900
I did not kill my father!

1047
01:10:30,900 --> 01:10:34,900
And I'd be inclined to believe you, because,

1048
01:10:34,900 --> 01:10:37,580
to do this,

1049
01:10:37,580 --> 01:10:40,740
to inflict this amount of pain...

1050
01:10:40,740 --> 01:10:45,380
and I am assured he would have been in extreme agony... Well...

1051
01:10:45,380 --> 01:10:49,620
There are simpler and less suspicious ways

1052
01:10:49,620 --> 01:10:51,860
to dispatch a father.

1053
01:10:51,860 --> 01:10:53,820
However, in your latest statement,

1054
01:10:53,820 --> 01:11:00,100
you still insist that you walked down to the quayside with your wife.

1055
01:11:01,980 --> 01:11:06,260
The truth, Mr Schmeikel, might just save your life.

1056
01:11:07,380 --> 01:11:09,460
However, if you persist...

1057
01:11:09,460 --> 01:11:13,060
It was too suspicious to say that I was there on my own.

1058
01:11:13,060 --> 01:11:17,020
I am being investigated for stealing from my father.

1059
01:11:17,020 --> 01:11:18,700
Oh.

1060
01:11:18,700 --> 01:11:20,620
Good. Better...

1061
01:11:22,140 --> 01:11:25,660
So, who saw you on your own?

1062
01:11:25,660 --> 01:11:28,340
The Hardyments.

1063
01:11:28,340 --> 01:11:30,740
They were the first to pass you, yeah?

1064
01:11:30,740 --> 01:11:32,500
The first, no.

1065
01:11:32,500 --> 01:11:35,220
The only ones. There were no others.

1066
01:11:37,220 --> 01:11:42,140
Mr Schmeikel, you were seen and passed by two cars.

1067
01:11:42,140 --> 01:11:44,860
No, by the Hardyments only.

1068
01:11:45,780 --> 01:11:47,740
There were no other cars!

1069
01:11:47,740 --> 01:11:51,140
You're telling me, no other cars?!

1070
01:11:54,260 --> 01:11:57,020
Parked cars, yes.

1071
01:11:57,020 --> 01:11:59,180
One on the street and one on the harbour.

1072
01:11:59,180 --> 01:12:01,580
The harbour one. What make?

1073
01:12:03,100 --> 01:12:05,900
A small family car.

1074
01:12:05,900 --> 01:12:07,420
Blue, I think.

1075
01:12:09,100 --> 01:12:11,620
Where's Stratton? What room's he in?!

1076
01:12:11,620 --> 01:12:13,460
Oh, he's still not here, sir.

1077
01:12:34,380 --> 01:12:35,980
Mr Stratton.

1078
01:12:41,660 --> 01:12:43,420
Hello!

1079
01:12:43,420 --> 01:12:45,340
Mr Stratton!

1080
01:12:47,540 --> 01:12:48,780
Anybody!

1081
01:13:02,940 --> 01:13:04,540
BANGING

1082
01:13:10,620 --> 01:13:12,820
You all right, son? Yes, sir.

1083
01:13:16,300 --> 01:13:18,820
Where's the wife and daughter?

1084
01:13:18,820 --> 01:13:23,300
Upstairs, I think, but he went out maybe five, ten minutes ago.

1085
01:13:52,980 --> 01:13:54,660
What're yer doing?

1086
01:13:54,660 --> 01:13:56,100
Why are yer pulling us?!

1087
01:13:56,100 --> 01:13:58,540
Just taking a short cut. Wanna get to the top.

1088
01:13:58,540 --> 01:14:01,500
I don't want to. I don't like it.

1089
01:14:08,820 --> 01:14:11,980
TYRES SCREECH

1090
01:14:16,540 --> 01:14:17,900
No!

1091
01:14:17,900 --> 01:14:19,940
Come on, Alice.

1092
01:14:22,820 --> 01:14:24,340
Come on.

1093
01:14:48,420 --> 01:14:50,580
When was...

1094
01:14:50,580 --> 01:14:52,700
the best time up here?

1095
01:14:52,700 --> 01:14:54,220
When was that, do you reckon?

1096
01:14:55,780 --> 01:14:57,300
When it was frosty.

1097
01:15:00,900 --> 01:15:03,500
It was cold and frosty.

1098
01:15:03,500 --> 01:15:06,060
It was a cold and frosty morning!

1099
01:15:06,060 --> 01:15:09,180
I remember. The mist was down there, wasn't it?

1100
01:15:10,820 --> 01:15:13,580
Was...was like,

1101
01:15:13,580 --> 01:15:15,620
like we were in heaven!

1102
01:15:15,620 --> 01:15:19,740
Like, like me and you were angels.

1103
01:15:19,740 --> 01:15:21,180
Dad!

1104
01:15:25,740 --> 01:15:27,300
Let her go!

1105
01:15:27,300 --> 01:15:28,940
Stratton!

1106
01:15:28,940 --> 01:15:31,260
Let her go!

1107
01:15:50,740 --> 01:15:52,500
There's a good girl.

1108
01:15:53,900 --> 01:15:55,380
Come on.

1109
01:16:10,180 --> 01:16:11,220
Sir? What?

1110
01:16:11,220 --> 01:16:13,020
Call the station.

1111
01:16:13,020 --> 01:16:17,140
Tell them to release Jimmy Hardyment and Schmeikel.

1112
01:16:17,140 --> 01:16:20,060
And call an ambulance for Mrs Stratton.

1113
01:16:20,060 --> 01:16:21,540
Non-urgent.

1114
01:16:43,020 --> 01:16:44,620
Sergeant.

1115
01:16:44,620 --> 01:16:46,540
Whatever part you played, thank you.

1116
01:16:46,540 --> 01:16:48,580
Much appreciated, as you know.

1117
01:16:48,580 --> 01:16:51,220
Let's get this straight. I did nothing to help you.

1118
01:16:51,220 --> 01:16:53,740
The money's going back into your bank account.

1119
01:16:53,740 --> 01:16:57,660
Personally, I think you should be done for attempting to bribe a police officer.

1120
01:16:57,660 --> 01:17:02,260
You know, Sergeant, you are really quite an unpleasant chap.

1121
01:17:02,260 --> 01:17:06,500
Why don't you piss off back to where you came from?

1122
01:17:06,500 --> 01:17:10,460
Auf Wiedersehen, Herr Sergeant.

1123
01:17:13,340 --> 01:17:15,140
Trudi.

1124
01:17:16,260 --> 01:17:17,700
Sorry.

1125
01:17:31,220 --> 01:17:32,420
You joining us?

1126
01:17:36,380 --> 01:17:37,900
It's fate, isn't it?

1127
01:17:39,660 --> 01:17:42,220
I could've been anywhere on the moors that day.

1128
01:17:42,220 --> 01:17:46,020
And if Jim Hardyment hadn't've been there, I'd never have gone over.

1129
01:17:48,660 --> 01:17:50,900
But over I went,

1130
01:17:50,900 --> 01:17:54,220
and there's this smart German bloke,

1131
01:17:54,220 --> 01:17:57,620
laughing about being a bomber pilot,

1132
01:17:57,620 --> 01:18:01,300
and how he was shot down over the Tyne 20 years ago.

1133
01:18:03,900 --> 01:18:06,060
Laughing about it. Aye, man.

1134
01:18:06,060 --> 01:18:07,580
What?

1135
01:18:12,380 --> 01:18:15,380
1944, I'm out in Italy.

1136
01:18:15,380 --> 01:18:18,660
Yeah you were mentioned in dispatches, weren't you? Aye.

1137
01:18:18,660 --> 01:18:20,620
For killing three guards.

1138
01:18:22,260 --> 01:18:23,980
They were the enemy.

1139
01:18:23,980 --> 01:18:26,300
We'd been captured.

1140
01:18:26,300 --> 01:18:27,580
How did yer kill 'em?

1141
01:18:28,700 --> 01:18:31,380
I have admitted killing Gunter Schmeikel.

1142
01:18:31,380 --> 01:18:35,980
You broke their necks, didn't yer! There you are, there!!

1143
01:18:37,780 --> 01:18:40,260
